              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                The South Asian Liver Institute is a premier center for liver transplantation. Our experienced transplant team has performed over 2,000 successful liver transplants, providing a new lease on life for patients with end-stage liver disease.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                We offer a comprehensive transplant program that includes pre-transplant evaluation, state-of-the-art surgical procedures, and lifelong post-transplant care. Our living donor liver transplant program is one of the most active in the region.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Who Needs a Liver Transplant?</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Liver transplantation is considered for patients with end-stage liver disease, acute liver failure, or certain liver cancers. Common conditions requiring transplant include cirrhosis from hepatitis B or C, alcohol-related liver disease, non-alcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD), primary biliary cholangitis, and hepatocellular carcinoma within Milan criteria.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Types of Liver Transplants</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li><strong>Living Donor Liver Transplant:</strong> A healthy family member donates a portion of their liver, which regenerates in both donor and recipient.</li>
                <li><strong>Deceased Donor Liver Transplant:</strong> Full liver transplant from a deceased donor through the national organ allocation program.</li>
                <li><strong>Split Liver Transplant:</strong> One donor liver is divided between two recipients, typically an adult and a child.</li>
              </ul>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Our Transplant Success Rates</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                SALi maintains excellent transplant outcomes with one-year patient survival rates exceeding 90% and five-year survival rates above 80%, matching international standards. Our multidisciplinary team includes transplant surgeons, hepatologists, anesthesiologists, intensivists, and specialized nurses dedicated to optimal patient care.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Post-Transplant Care</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Following transplantation, patients receive comprehensive follow-up care including immunosuppression management, infection prevention, nutritional counseling, and regular monitoring. Our dedicated transplant coordinators guide patients through every step of their journey from evaluation to long-term follow-up.
              </p>
